\section{Results}

\subsection{Diagnostic Performance}

GPT-5 achieves 62\% accuracy (Table~\ref{tab:diag}), competitive
with the AgentClinic baseline range of 42--66\%~\cite{schmidgall2025agentclinic}.
In this preliminary 50-case evaluation, 4 cases (8\%) did not reach
a confident diagnosis within the 10-turn budget; these cases involve
conditions with low prior prevalence---Meigs syndrome, primary
sclerosing cholangitis, essential thrombocythemia, and hemophilia.
These percentages should be interpreted as early indicators, not
stable estimates, pending the full 200-case evaluation. Five cases
show premature action (final decision before turn 3). Mean decision
delay is 7.2 turns, indicating generally appropriate history
gathering before commitment.

