\subsection{Diagnostic Over-Ordering}

In the 66\% of cases where tests were ordered, GPT-5 requested a mean
of 5.54 tests per case with only 1.54 found in the clinical record
(precision 0.41, find rate 28\%, Table~\ref{tab:tests},
Fig.~\ref{fig:tests}). Extreme cases include Case~3 (diffuse large
B-cell lymphoma: 45 requests, 6 found, precision 0.13) and Case~25
(primary sclerosing cholangitis, never diagnosed: 37 requests, 12
found). The test-action mismatch rate of 18\% further reveals
inconsistency: in nearly one in five cases, REQUEST\_TEST appeared in
the free-text reasoning but the ACTION field specified a different
action.

