\subsection{Failure Mode Taxonomy}

The 19 incorrect diagnoses fall into four categories
(Fig.~\ref{fig:tests}, right). \textbf{Symptom overlap} (37\%, 7
cases): the model diagnosed a condition sharing the presenting cluster
without the correct underlying aetiology (e.g., Hirschsprung's disease
as intussusception; lung cancer as acute CO poisoning).
\textbf{Rare disease failure} (21\%, 4 cases): Meigs syndrome, PSC,
essential thrombocythemia, hemophilia---conditions whose low prior
prevalence prevents confident convergence. \textbf{High-harm miss}
(21\%, 4 cases): wrong diagnosis plus high-risk action with no
guardrail intervention---the most dangerous failure mode.
\textbf{Clinically adjacent} (21\%, 4 cases): predictions differing
by specificity rather than disease class; some may represent
LLM-judge errors rather than true misdiagnoses.

